<div class="section padded-md">
	<h2>Wrappers</h2>
	<p>
		Sometimes you want to build sites that contain wrapped and unwrapped elements. Creating unwrapped elements that later contain wrapped elements is as simple as adding the <code>.wrapped</code> class to your element, then putting that element in an <code>.unwrapped</code> container.
	</p>
</div>

<div class="section unwrapped bg-qubared fg-white">
	<div class="section wrapped padded-md">
		<p class="reset">This content sits inside a wrapped section, which sits inside an unwrapped section.</p>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="section padded-md">
	<p class="reset">There is also a <code>.breakout</code> class which you can apply to get this:</p>
</div>

<div class="section breakout padded-md bg-qubared fg-white">
	<p class="reset">Breakout</p>
</div>

<div class="section padded-md">
	<p>You can change how far the breakout should break using the <code>$wrapper-breakout-width</code> variable.</p>
	<p class="reset">You can mix and match classes to achieve other desired layouts.</p>
</div>

<div class="section unwrapped bg-qubared fg-white">
	<div class="section wrapped padded-md">
		<div class="section breakout">
			Breakout inside wrapped inside unwrapped
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<br>

<div class="unwrapped bg-qubared fg-white">
	<p>Completely unwrapped</p>
</div>
